Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. Press any key to continue...

.P.S. im using the downloaded source compiler, i havn't made my own one. I dont know if that makes a difference, but if it does please tell me how to make one. I'm using - jdk.1.6.0_20
THANK YOU

item.title: I cannot compile?!? (READ ALL PLEASE!)
item.dc:creator: @Fire_capez Fire capez
item.description:
@Fire_capez wrote:

[quote=“travisabbott, post:3, topic:347604”]but i changed player rights while my character was logged off, and then i compiled…

but when i log in i have no owner privileges and when i log back out my player rights have changed automatically back to 0 in my source characters…[/quote]

You do not have to compile when editing .txt files.
Also you must be logged off in order for your characters to update when you are editing them. (Due to the fact they autosave).
